Technical quality:sub-optimal imaging due to patient position, supine on trolley LEFT VENTRICLE: Impression of mild to moderately impaired LV systolic function. No dilatation. No LVH. RWMAs: apex, entire inferior and septal walls appear impaired. Visually estimated EF 40-45% Measurements: IVS = 0.9 cm, PWd = 0.9 cm, LVIDd = 5.4 cm, LVIDs = 4.1 cm. unable to assess diastolic function Lateral peak SÍ velocity 0.1m/s, septal peak SÍ 0.06m/s. auto EF = 67%. MITRAL VALVE: Thin and mobile leaflets. Opens well. Mild regurgitation. LEFT ATRIUM: Severely dilated (area 31 cm2, volume 100 mls) AORTIC VALVE: Appears trileaflet, opens well. leaflets appear mildly thickened. Trivial to mild aortic regurgitation. Peak forward flow velocity 1.5m/s. Aortic root not dilated. Sinus of Valsalva 3.2cm, sinotubular junction 2.8cm (indexed 17mm/m) , ascending aorta 2.2cm. No coarctation. RIGHT VENTRICLE: Mildly impaired right ventricular function. No dilatation. No RVH. TAPSE 1.1 cm Right atrium appears dilated visually TRICUSPID VALVE: Trivial tricuspid regurgitation, Estimated PASP 21mmHg + RAP IVC not dilated, collapses on inspiration. PULMONARY VALVE: Opens well. No PR. MISC: No pericardial effusion. SUMMARY: Impression of mild to moderately impaired LV systolic function. No dilatation. No LVH. RWMAs noted. Visually estimated EF 40-45% Mildly impaired RV function. Estimated PASP 21mmHg + RAP Trivial to mild aortic regurgitation Mild MR & TR Dilated atria Scanned and r

IMAGE QUALITY: Sub optimal apical imaging ECHO MACHINE: GE Vivid 7 ECG: Sinus rhythm (average rate 75bpm) Echocardiographer LEFT VENTRICLE: Normal LV cavity size with normal wall thickness Preserved post op systolic function, hypokinesis of the septum, other walls appear to contract well No significant diastolic dysfunction LV MEASUREMENTS: IVSd 1.1cm, LVIDd 3.8cm, PWd 1.2cm, LVIDs 2.6cm LVEF estimated visually at 55% E/A ratio 2.1, DcT 233ms, Avg E/Eprime 8, S vel sept 7cm/s, S vel lateral 7cm/s LEFT ATRIUM: Mildly dilated left atrium. Area 25cm.sq MITRAL VALVE: Structurally and functionally normal mitral valve with no mitral regurgitation noted AORTIC VALVE: Trileaflet aortic valve with normal forward flow velocities, AV Vmx is 1.6m/s. No aortic regurgitation noted AORTA: Normal dimension of the aortic root Sinuses 3.0cm, ST junction 2.8cm (1.3cm/m), Ascending aorta 3.0cm Normal appearance of the aortic arch with no obvious evidence of co-arctation RIGHT SIDED STRUCTURES: Normal RV size with reduced radial and long axis function consistent with previous cardiac surgery TAPSE 17, RV S Vel 0.07m/s Normal RA size, area cm.sq IVC is of normal size with normal respiratory variation Tricuspid valve is structurally and functionally normal Insufficient TR to accurately assess PASP Pulmonary valve is functionally normal PERICARDIUM: Normal appearance of the pericardium with no obvious pericardial effusion noted SUMMARY: Normal LV cavity size with preserved post op systolic function, septum is hypokinetic, LVEF estimated at 55% No significant diastolic dysfunction Normal RV size with reduced systolic function consistent with recent cardiac surgery Atria are of normal size No significant valvular abnormalities noted No significant pericardial effusion
